Former VBS Bank CFO, Philip Truter, has appeared in the Specialised Commercial Crimes Court in Palm Ridge. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former VBS Mutual Bank CFO, Philip Truter has been granted bail of R50,000 and intends to plead guilty. Truter appeared in the Specialised Commercial Crimes Court in Palm Ridge on Monday. READ: Another VBS suspect arrested He's the 8th suspect arrested in connection with the VBS bank heist. The seven other suspects were granted bail of R100,000 each. Over R2-billion went missing from VBS Mutual Bank.